import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data = data.groupby('Year').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['count'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of disasters over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Disasters')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Entity').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values('counts', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['Entity'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Disaster Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of disaster?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Deaths'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Number of Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths resulting from disasters?')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    data = data.groupby(['Entity', 'Year']).sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    for entity in data['Entity'].unique():
        entity_data = data[data['Entity'] == entity]
        ax.plot(entity_data['Year'], entity_data['Deaths'], label=entity)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of deaths resulting from a specific type of disaster?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
